From 2e6889e496fdc82eae6181b95e1aa9c26fd48ecd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kierandrewett <kieran@drewett.dev>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 09:28:51 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] tooling: per-app persistent ScreenCast/RemoteDesktop grants

Replace the blanket GNOBLIN_PORTAL_AUTOGRANT bypass with a macOS-style,
per-app persistent grant store that gnoblin owns.

Apps that round-trip a restore_token already skip the consent dialog.
Apps that do not (e.g. rustdesk) hit the picker/consent dialog on every
session. This adds a per-app grant so the user can approve once via an
"Always allow this app" checkbox and connect unattended thereafter.

Grant store (src/utils.c):
  - gnoblin_portal_grant_id(): stable, filesystem-safe id. Uses app_id
    when non-empty; otherwise derives from the D-Bus sender's executable
    basename (GetConnectionUnixProcessID -> /proc/PID/exe) so unsandboxed
    apps with an empty app_id still get a stable per-binary id.
  - gnoblin_portal_app_granted(): TRUE if the marker file
    $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gnoblin/portal-grants/<grant_id> exists.
  - gnoblin_portal_store_grant(): create that marker (mkdir -p).

ScreenCast/RemoteDesktop handle_start() stash the grant id on the session
and, only when a grant already exists, take the existing fast path
(select every monitor + start_session) instead of showing the dialog.
The dialogs gain an "Always allow this app" checkbox whose approval calls
gnoblin_portal_store_grant().

Default behaviour is unchanged: with no stored grant the dialog is shown.
Nothing is ever granted unconditionally.
